standard_metadata.standard_description: Fluently add and subtract multi-digit whole numbers using the standard algorithm.

images.alt: A stacked subtraction problem showing how to regroup digits when subtracting. The equation shows 389002 minus 75151. So, 2 ones minus 1 one is 1 one. Next to the stacked equation is 2 minus 1 equals 1.

A stacked subtraction problem showing how to regroup digits when subtracting. The equation shows 389002 minus 75151. The 389002 becomes 3 hundred-thousands, 8 ten-thousands, 8 thousands, 9 hundreds, 10 tens and 2 ones. So, 10 tens minus 5 tens is 5 tens. Next to the stacked equation is 100 minus 50 equals 50.

A stacked subtraction problem showing how to regroup digits when subtracting. The equation shows 389002 minus 75151. The 389002 becomes 3 hundred-thousands, 8 ten-thousands, 8 thousands, 9 hundreds, 0 tens and 2 ones. So, 9 hundreds minus 1 hundred is 8 hundreds. Next to the stacked equation is 900 minus 100 equals 800.

A stacked subtraction problem showing how to regroup digits when subtracting. The equation shows 389002 minus 75151. Next to the stacked equation is 8000 minus 6000 equals 2000.

A stacked subtraction problem showing how to regroup digits when subtracting. The equation shows 389002 minus 75151. So, 8 ten-thousands minus 7 ten-thousands is 1 ten-thousand. Next to the stacked equation is 80000 minus 70000 equals 10000.
